 49 Dazzle will stick only on mobs lvl 55 and less.   The difference between these is duration - I still love Dazzle for its long duration.<br>
<br>
Once you start facing mobs that are 56+, you need higher spells for that.<br>
<br>
Glamour of Kintaz(54):  -10 resist adjust, works on mobs up to level 57.  Yeah, only 2 levels above Dazzle, but you'll be surprized how many lvl 56-57 mobs are out there.<br>
<br>
Rapture(59)/Ancient: Eternal Rapture(60)  The pre-pop big gun.  Mezzes mobs up to lvl 61, and have -1000 adjust.  It means that unless mob is immune, it will mez it, regardless of MR.<br>
<br>
Once you start getting into tier 2 of PoP, you need your 61+ spells:<br>
Apathy(61) will mez up to lvl 62 mobs.   Only 1 level above Rapture, but Rapture has 24 sec recast - while Apathy is ~2 sec.  You cannot hold 2 lvl 61 adds with Rapture. <br>
<br>
Sleep(63) works on mobs up to 65, and is essential for deep Tier 2 and for Tier 3.  <br>
<br>
Finally, bliss(64) will mez mobs up to lvl 68, and will be real handy in elemental planes. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
