<br>
Research on Alla's shows that the moktors can by level 53 to 57 so I guess most of them are 55-57.  The fallen soldiers should be level 51-53 according to alla's, so I should have bene able to mez them.  I'll have to doublecheck my log files to make sure it was the soldiers that also were showing up at too high level.<br>
<br>
This tells me that if it doesn't take my group long to kill mobs, then a lower level mez is more mana efficient, but more dangerous on pulls with more than one add.  I've always just used the highest level mez that I have, though the mana cost of 'current level' spells always seems to hurt compared to previous level spells :-)<br>
<br>
This also tells me that I have a long way to go (exp wise, 49-54) before I get a mez that I could use on reliably in umbral.  I'll have to research mob levels more carefully now that I'm approaching my max level to be able to mez based on the raids I've been on.  In normal experience groups I don't expect it will be a problem for awhile ye.<br>
