<br>
The giants there are mezzable (some).  Some are casters and others are pure melee.  Always remember to keep the casters mezzed take them out last.  Even if the add is a melee only target.  The reason is because I have had situations where the group is fighting a caster....and a melee mob comes into camp that I have had to mezz.  Only to have the caster that the group is fighting <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>dispel my mezzed mob</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
The casters will dispel mezzed targets, which can really screw up your crowd control. <p><center><img border=0 src="http://www.speakeasy.org/~robtony/cattsiggy.jpg" /></center><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381558" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://www.speakeasy.org/~robtony/catcorpse.jpg" /></center></a><BR><center><img border=0 src="http://www.speakeasy.org/~robtony/quote_corna2.jpg"/></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dulsin>Dulsin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(7/15/03 12:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=272.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level of creature you can mez?</span><hr size=1> Once you hit 59 you can start Mezzing again. <br>
